# React Conventions

## Component Style

- Prefer functional components over class components
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Use Material-UI (MUI) components
- Use Apollo Client for GraphQL

## File Naming

- PascalCase for component files: `EntityCard.tsx`
- camelCase for hooks: `useGraphData.ts`
- Index files for exports: `index.ts`

## Example Component

```typescript
import React from 'react';
import { Card, CardContent, Typography } from '@mui/material';

interface EntityCardProps {
  entity: {
    id: string;
    name: string;
    type: string;
  };
}

export const EntityCard: React.FC<EntityCardProps> = ({ entity }) => {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardContent>
        <Typography variant="h5">{entity.name}</Typography>
        <Typography color="textSecondary">{entity.type}</Typography>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
};
```

## Hooks

- Prefix custom hooks with `use`
- Handle loading and error states
- Clean up effects properly

```typescript
export function useEntity(id: string) {
  const { data, loading, error } = useQuery(GET_ENTITY, {
    variables: { id },
  });

  return {
    entity: data?.entity,
    loading,
    error,
  };
}
```
